Hello,
Many of wordpress users find difficult to send e-mails to users by using server mail id. Like for regstraion verfication link, welocme email etc. By default wordpress php mailer all mail goes to spams. 
So how to setup the mail configuration in wordpress.

Step 1 - Create a server mail id on your hosting like godaddy, bluehost. 
1.a -> After creating the id, go to mail configuration (settings) in your cpanel , there you will see outgoing mail configuration SMTP settings.
1.b -> Copy the Outgoing server name, port, username and password in atext file.

